# Search Index & Sitemap: New Content Checklist

When adding new content to the site, you MUST ensure it is discoverable via search and sitemap.

## Mandatory Updates

**When adding any of the following, update BOTH scripts:**

| Content Type | Search Index (`web/scripts/generate-search-index.js`) | Sitemap (`web/scripts/generate-sitemap.js`) |
|--------------|--------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| New planner/guide page | Add to `planners` array | Add `add(baseUrl + '/planners/your-page/', ...)` |
| New best-of ranking | Add to `rankings` array | Auto-discovered from `out/best-of/` |
| New comparison pair | Add to `COMPARISON_PAIRS` | Auto-discovered from `out/compare/` |
| New Information article | Add to `infoPages` array | Auto-discovered from `out/information/` |
| New topic type (e.g. climate) | Add to `topicLabels` in index | Auto-discovered from town topic dirs |
| New tool page | Add to "Other pages" section | Add explicit `add()` if not under scanned dirs |

## Auto-Discovered (No Manual Update Needed)

These are pulled from data files or build output—new entries are included automatically:

- **Towns** — from `cities_towns_list/towns.txt`
- **Corridors** — from `web/data/corridors.json`
- **Hot springs** — from `web/data/hot-springs.json`
- **Campgrounds** — from `web/data/campgrounds.json`
- **Trails** — from `web/data/hiking.json`
- **Moving guides** — one per town (from towns list)
- **Town topic pages** — for new hub dirs under `web/components/town/topics/`
- **Sitemap**: guides, best-of, compare, Information, town topics — scanned from `out/` after build

## Workflow

1. Add the new page or data.
2. If it's a **new page type** (planner, article, tool): update both `generate-search-index.js` and `generate-sitemap.js`.
3. If it's **new data** (town, corridor, hot spring, etc.): no script changes—next build includes it.
4. Run `npm run build` in `web/` to regenerate index and sitemap.
5. Verify: `web/public/search-index.json` and `web/out/sitemap.xml` contain the new content.

## Reference

- Search index: `web/scripts/generate-search-index.js` (runs in `prebuild`)
- Sitemap: `web/scripts/generate-sitemap.js` (runs after `next export`)
